subject: Do not serve partial img download reqs from cache

values.-1: This patch needs further work before it can be merged
values.+1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

messages.message: Uploaded patch set 1.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This looks good from a quick look. I'm wondering whether we should fix process_request as well for partial image downloads. I mean, when a partial image download is received, bypass the cache and let the rootapp serve the request irrespective of whether the image is cached or not. 

I'm thinking this is required because the moment we push this patch, the partial image download request will start failing in process_request. So, I'm inclining towards fixing process_request as well.

Once we get this backported, we can work on a separate patch that serves the partial image download request from cached image. Thoughts?

Patch Set 1:

Sure Hemanth.
The partial download image request will fail in process_request with or without PS1.
Will ensure we serve from store even for an already cached image.

Playing with the change to cache.py seems to work correctly for an uncached image:

uri = 'http://10.134.13.103:9292/v2/images/%s/file' % image_id
content_range = 'bytes 0-32/*'

# build headers
headers = {'X-Auth-Token': sess.get_token(),
           'Content-Range': content_range
}

response = requests.get(uri, headers=headers)
print response
print response.headers

->

<Response [206]>
{'Content-Length': '33', 'Content-Md5': 'eb9139e4942121f22bbc2afc0400b2a4', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Date': 'Thu, 16 Feb 2017 16:14:39 GMT', 'Content-Type': 'application/octet-stream', 'X-Openstack-Request-Id': 'req-ff01cda1-f259-4d1d-a502-b0caa3beac6d'}


If I download the full image and try the partial download again, it also seems to work:

<Response [206]>

So, the changes look good to me.  Thanks for fixing this!
